          "guid": "mrxyaiily8qr9w6p",
          "message": {
            "text": "The two KF-381 shapes are pinned as .skip tests asserting the INTENDED contract, not as passing tests asserting the buggy duplicate-rows output. Rationale: asserting duplication as expected would make the KF-381 fix a red-to-green flip in the wrong direction and would put a wrong contract in the suite; .skip keeps the correct contract readable, and un-skipping these two tests is the fix's acceptance criterion. The npm run check gate stays green because skipped tests don't run.",
            "markdown": "The two KF-381 shapes are pinned as .skip tests asserting the INTENDED contract, not as passing tests asserting the buggy duplicate-rows output. Rationale: asserting duplication as expected would make the KF-381 fix a red-to-green flip in the wrong direction and would put a wrong contract in the suite; .skip keeps the correct contract readable, and un-skipping these two tests is the fix's acceptance criterion. The npm run check gate stays green because skipped tests don't run."
          },
